title: Datafam APAC Catch-Up 2023/10
description_short: Join the fun. Chat with the local community, ask for help and have a good time!
chapter_description:
The Datafam Catch-Ups came to life because of a desire to catch up with the community, when international travel was difficult.

These days it's a great way to stay in touch with community members across countries and regions or to meet new people.

We run monthly sessions without much of an agenda. Depending on participation, we might split up into breakout rooms, play games, help each other or just chat.

Join one of our sessions and just say "Hello"!

title: TUG Zurich @Merkle with guest talk on great-looking visual tables by Visionary Klaus Schulte
description_short:
Our host company Merkle drives projects with Tableau and shares insights with us all!

Don't miss Dr. Klaus Schulte, Tableau Ambassador, #IronViz Competitor and world-known Tableau Expert
Tableau Visionary Klaus Schulte sharing his best tips and tricks for creating great-looking visual tables in Tableau.

See you at Merkle - midst of Zurich and in walking distance of Zurich Hardbrücke.
chapter_description:
Welcome to the Zurich Tableau User Group!

We are a vibrant community of Tableau users hailing from the wider Zurich area. Our group provides a unique opportunity for individuals passionate about Tableau, Tableau Server, Data, and Storytelling to connect and learn together.

By gathering in person, we foster an environment that encourages hands-on learning and knowledge sharing. Whether you're a seasoned Tableau expert or just starting your data visualization journey, our meetings are designed to cater to all skill levels. We firmly believe that the power of collective intelligence lies in the diversity of our members' experiences and backgrounds.

Our group discussions delve into a wide range of topics, including best practices, success stories, and critical challenges faced by Tableau users. Through these conversations, we gain valuable insights and practical knowledge that empower us to enhance our own data visualization skills.

But it's not just about learning and professional growth; it's also about having fun and building a strong community. We believe that a supportive and collaborative environment fosters both personal and professional development. So, expect engaging interactions, lively discussions, and lasting connections with fellow data enthusiasts.

The Zurich Tableau User Group warmly welcomes anyone with an interest in Tableau and the world of data visualization. Whether you're a data analyst, data scientist, business intelligence professional, or simply curious about Tableau's capabilities, we invite you to join us and become an active member of our community.

We - Ueli Basler and Benny Saladin, the Zurich Tableau User Group organizers - are excited to have you on board. We look forward to welcoming you as a member and embarking on this enriching Tableau journey together!

Join us now and let's explore the exciting world of Tableau!

Note: Please visit our official website or reach out to us directly for information on upcoming events, meeting locations, and membership details.

description_short:
The Prague Tableau User Group meeting is a great opportunity for networking, where attendees have the chance to meet and connect with other Tableau enthusiasts. 
Those events are focused on creating a place for sharing knowledge, allowing participants to exchange insights and ideas. 
Our host is ACTUM DIGITAL, Holesovice. 
At the end of the event we will continue the fun by heading to a pub.
chapter_description:
Prague TUG (PRGTUG) is an open Tableau User Group (TUG) based in Prague, Czech Republic. It is for all customers, fans and enthusiasts of Tableau.

Whenever you are a beginner, a wizard, or just curious, you are welcome to join the group!

title: PDX TUG Tableau Learning: Beginner, Intermediate, Advanced. Come one come all!
description_short: This month we've got something for everyone! A quick crash course on Tableau, a how to on Parameters, and what the heck are LOD's?? All this and more will be covered.

title: Primer encuentro: conozca la nueva comunidad de usuarios de Tableau Costa Rica
description_short: Hemos creado el capítulo Costa Rica para apoyar nuestra comunidad de usuarios Tableau,  el objetivo principal consiste en consolidar una comunidad de apoyo, compartir recursos y conocimiento, actualizarnos de lo que ofrece la plataforma Tableau, hacer networking y mas actividades de colaboración.
chapter_description:
Somos un grupo de entusiastas en el uso de la Plataforma Tableau, enfocados en aportar valor en las organizaciones y mayores conocimientos en la cultura analítica de datos para su desarrollo profesional, aportando para abrir mayores oportunidades de empleo y de negocio. 

Tableau es parte del Data-Driven Path que debe ser necesario conocer, profundizar e implementar en las organizaciones para que se facilite la toma de decisiones basadas en datos. En este grupo estaremos realizando actividades de generación de conocimiento, entender el futuro de esta plataforma e integración con otras tecnologías, hacemos transferencia de conocimiento y disfrutaremos socializando con personas de nuestro mismo idioma y objetivos profesionales.

title: Do it on Public: Leveraging Tableau Public, the World's Largest Visualization Platform
description_short: Discover the power of leveraging Tableau Public, the world's largest visualization platform. Enhance your visualization and technical skills, get inspired and showcase your data visualization skills.

title: Tableau High Availability & Self-Service Analytics
description_short: Explore Tableau Server clustering for high availability and learn to empower your team with self-service analytics
chapter_description:
The Cyprus Tableau User Group is a community of professionals, academics, and data enthusiasts who share a common interest in data visualization and analysis using Tableau software. The group provides a forum for Tableau users to connect, learn, and share their experiences and best practices with others in the community. 

The group is open to anyone interested in Tableau, regardless of their level of expertise or background. Whether you're a seasoned Tableau user or just getting started, the Cyprus Tableau User Group offers a supportive and collaborative environment for exploring the world of data visualization and analysis. 

By participating in the group, members have the opportunity to expand their knowledge of Tableau, develop new skills, and build relationships with other Tableau users in the community. 

Overall, the Cyprus Tableau User Group is a dynamic and engaging community of Tableau users who are passionate about exploring the possibilities of data visualization and analysis using Tableau software.

title: Data + Diversity: Fireside Chat with Lilia Luciano (in Spanish)
description_short: En celebración del Mes de la Herencia Hispana, únete a una charla inspiradora junto a la chimenea con Lilia Luciano, una destacada figura del periodismo. Lilia es una periodista galardonada, directora de documentales, productora, podcaster y conferencista que actualmente se desempeña como corresponsal de la cadena de noticias CBS News.
chapter_description: “Together, we are extraordinary,” is the foundation of the Tableau Community which makes our commitment to diversity, inclusion, and equality more important than ever before. We recognize diversity not only makes for better companies, but unlocks the potential of individuals and the community as a whole. Understanding diversity data can be difficult, and data is a powerful tool to help bring accountability to diversity efforts. Join us monthly for virtual conversations on diversity advocacy and experiences from our data community. With Data + Diversity, we'll highlight voices and share actionable ways to use data for greater inclusion, and provide much-needed inspiration for active change.

title: Simple But Not Basic: Avoiding the Pumpkin Spice Latte of Dashboard Designs
description_short: Our guest speaker, Paul Wiklanski from the University of Michigan, has astutely observed a common challenge in dashboard development: the allure of fancy features and an excess of dashboards can overwhelm users. His solution? The pursuit of intentional simplicity, as he understands that users crave streamlined experiences that support fundraising strategies.
chapter_description:
Welcome! This group is for advancement professionals (in education, non-profit, and NGOs) who are Tableau users and developers at all skill levels, or interested in fundraising analytics. Let’s share ideas, best practices, and strategies for visualizing advancement data in Tableau.

Mission: To connect Advancement professionals to make them more productive and successful.

Vision: We passionately believe in the power of instilling confidence in and providing opportunities to high potential individuals, and ultimately helping them become the next generation of leaders.

title: Data+Women Lunch Series with Evelyn Münster, the Chart Doktor
description_short:
With her Chart Doktor trainings Evelyn helps data analysts create data products that are actually being used and loved by business users. The focus is readability, adoption, actionable insights and business value.

Her "Cycle of Encoding and Decoding" is the basis for data literacy education at German universities.

title: London Financial Services TUG @The Information Lab - October
description_short: On October 12th, the Financial Services Tableau User Group will be meeting to discuss industry-specific use cases and share their experiences with Tableau in the financial services sector. Join your Financial Services community in our third session of the year, this time at the The Information Lab offices in City.
chapter_description: We want to create a space for Tableau users in the Financial Services sector to foster collaboration, growth, learn and network. We meet on a quarterly basis in different places around London to discuss how can we best leverage Tableau in the Financial sector. Previous speakers include Lloyds Banking Group, Deutsche Bank, Invesco, NatWest, J.P. Morgan, Aldermore, Charles Stanley and more.
chapter_title: UK Financial Services Tableau User Group

description_short: Do you want to get everything out of the Dashboard Performance? Alexander Schaack will blow you away with the tips and tricks so your dashboard is faster than Usain Bolt. Our second keynote is less technical and rich in experience: Marc Bäuerle talks about his process on a dashboard project. From A-Z, using a real use case. As always: be prepared to be informed and entertained!
chapter_description: We are Munich locals, our meetings are in English and in-person only. Our community is special because we are active in discussions, we openly share pains and make them gains and every meeting we have one community member who is our keynote speaker. From the community, for the community! Coffee, Lunch and networking make our events agreeable - join us for donuts on your charts and on your plate!

title: Visionary's Guide for Tableau Cloud/Server Security (3/3)
description_short: Data security is everyone's top concern. This talk will focus on additional data security watchdog scripts to further enhance the data security on Tableau server. Like inactive user detection and deletion, content archiving, how to avoid users subscribed and forgot? How to deal with 'All Users' group? How to deal with PII and sensitive data on server?
chapter_title: Tableau Server & Cloud Admin User Group
